  13 Sep 2013; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Drop python-json dependency, all supported Python versions ship json in
  stdlib now.

  06 Sep 2013; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Drop Python 2.5 support.

  08 May 2013; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Use $PYTHON_USEDEP, where possible.

  17 Mar 2013; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Added missing simplejson dependency.

  20 Dec 2012; Matt Leighy <mleighy@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Use ranges for PYTHON_COMPAT readability.

  19 Dec 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Updated for distutils-r1 usage.

  26 Nov 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Switched to EAPI-5.

  01 Nov 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Switched to virtual/python-argparse.

  31 Jul 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Don't run python-distutils-ng_redoscript, as recent silent updates to
  python-distutils-ng now run it and break packages.

  09 Apr 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  PATCHES src_prepare workaround now in jnrowe-pypi eclass.

  08 Apr 2012; James Rowe <jnrowe@gmail.com> jsonpipe-0.0.8-r1.ebuild:
  Switched to python-distutils-ng eclass.

